section.section:
The notices required under this subsection shall include at least the following:
a statement of the fact of the issuance of a certificate of sale;
a copy of the certificate of sale, if the holder of the certificate of sale received the certificate of sale before the notice was sent under this paragraph;
a statement that the owner, a mortgage holder, or any other person that has an estate or interest in the property may redeem the property at any time until the right of redemption has been finally foreclosed under the provisions of this subtitle;
a statement that the holder of the certificate of sale may file an action to foreclose the right of redemption at any time after 2 months from the date of the first notice;
a statement that if the property is redeemed before an action to foreclose the right of redemption is filed, the amount that shall be paid to redeem the property is:
the total lien amount on the property at the time of sale, with interest;
any taxes, interest, and penalties paid by the holder of the certificate of sale;
any taxes, interest, and penalties accruing after the date of the tax sale; and
the following expenses incurred by the holder of the certificate of sale:
a statement that if the property is redeemed after an action to foreclose the right of redemption has been filed, the amount that shall be paid to redeem the property is the sum of:
the total lien amount on the property at the time of sale, with interest;
any taxes, interest, and penalties paid by the holder of the certificate of sale;
any taxes, interest, and penalties accruing after the date of the tax sale; and
attorney's fees and expenses to which the holder of the certificate of sale may be entitled under § 14-843(a)(4) and (5) of this subtitle;
the provisions of § 14-843(a) of this subtitle, reproduced as they appear in the Code;
a statement that, in Baltimore City only, the holder of the certificate of sale is entitled to taxes, interest, and penalties paid in accordance with § 14-843(c) of this subtitle and interest at the rate of redemption under § 14-820 of this subtitle from the date of payment to the date of redemption; and
the name, address, and telephone number of:
the holder of the certificate of sale, or the holder's agent or attorney; and
the collector who made the sale.
